"adj. 戏剧的，演戏的 【英】 adj.戏剧的，演戏的 (relating to drama; dramatic) 【记】 来自古希腊悲剧创始 者Thespis adj. 戏剧性的(一般是悲剧) 【记】源于古希腊悲剧创始者Thespis(泰斯庇斯)the神, s, pian骗: 被神骗死了－悲剧的戏剧的. 【记】音：戏片，戏剧影片，比如动作戏片，爱情戏片；音：写实片，叙述片 都是电影戏剧片；音：戏西班牙，西班牙戏剧很出名，卡门，费加罗的婚礼等，全是写西班牙的； thespian (adj.)  1670s, ""of or pertaining to tragedy or dramatic acting,"" from Greek Thespis, semi-legendary 6c. B.C.E. poet of Icaria in Attica, often called the Father of Greek Tragedy. The literal meaning of the name is ""inspired by the gods."" thespian (n.)  ""an actor,"" 1827, from thespian (adj.). Short form thesp is attested from 1962."
